# 5. 遠い記憶の花畑

Mizuki: Hey, white carnations! I always see red or pink ones, but these white ones are really pretty too!
Mizuki: Do you like carnations, Kanade?
Kanade: Oh, uh... Not me... My mom did...
Kanade: She always kept some around the house, and I bring her these every time I go visit her grave.
Mizuki: I see...
Kanade: I'm sorry. I didn't mean to...
Mizuki: No, it's okay. I'm sorry for asking without really thinking it through first.
Mizuki: But flowers are great, aren't they? They have this therapeutic quality to them...
Mizuki: It'd be great to even see a whole field of them. One with lavenders and sunflowers... It'd be so beautiful...!
Kanade: A field of flowers...
Kanade: I vaguely remember my dad taking us to see one a long time ago.
Mizuki: Really? Like a field of carnations...?
Kanade: Yes. It was fairly close by too, I think. I remember being surprised by how you could see something like that in the city.
Mizuki: Yeah, that is pretty surprising!
Kanade: But I remember having so much fun then... The weather was nice and everyone was laughing...
Mizuki: Hey, Kanade. Wanna try finding that flower field together?
Kanade: Huh?
Mizuki: It's somewhere around here, right? There's only a few places in the city where something like that could be, so I'm sure we'll find it pretty quick!
Kanade: But it's still raining... Are you sure?
Mizuki: Yeah, totally! I've got my favorite rainboots on too, so it'd be nice to get a little more mileage on them!
Kanade: Thanks, Mizuki...
Mizuki: Then let's start with... Miyamasuzaka Park. That's been there forever, and it's huge!
Kanade: Okay. Let's try there.
Mizuki: Man... We've checked out every park around here, but nothing...
Kanade: Yeah...
Kanade: Maybe I'm confusing it with somewhere else. It might not actually be in the city like I said.
Kanade: I'm so sorry for making you do this. Especially considering the weather...
Mizuki: Don't worry about that, Kanade!
Mizuki: Let's just keep looking, alright? It could still be on the other side of the station, you know?
Kanade: No it's okay. Let's stop for now. Thank you for doing this.
Mizuki: Kanade...
Mizuki: Sorry I couldn't help you find it...
Mizuki: But maybe some other time we can...
Mizuki: ...
Mizuki: (But when...?)
Mizuki: (Will I still be friends with her when that time comes...?)
Kanade: Mizuki...?
Mizuki: Uh... N-Nothing. It's nothing. Something was bugging me is all.
Mizuki: But you're heading back to the station, right? We can use this park as a shortcut to get there.
Kanade: Okay.
Mizuki: This rain really isn't letting up, huh? All we've been getting lately is bad weather too...
Mizuki: But you might even think of a good song when it's finally sunny again, so I wouldn't fret too much, Kanade.
Mizuki: And whenever you feel like hanging out again, you know who to call!
Kanade: Right, I'll keep that in mind.
Kanade: It was nice doing something like this for a change.
Mizuki: Really? That's great!
Kanade: To tell you the truth, I went to visit my dad today...
Mizuki: Your dad?
Kanade: Yes.
Kanade: Ever since he had his breakdown, his memory's become jumbled. He talked about the time before I was born today...
Kanade: He seemed so happy too...
Kanade: Then it reminded me of how I took away his happiness. I felt so awful afterwards...
Mizuki: Kanade...
Kanade: That was when I thought that I have to compose a song that can save Mafuyu as soon as I can.
Kanade: I convinced myself that I had no right to be there unless I did that first...
Kanade: But I feel much better after you took me around to visit all these other places, Mizuki...
Kanade: So thank you.
Mizuki: Don't mention it...
Mizuki: (Kanade...)
Mizuki: (She thinks what happened to her dad is all her fault and is making songs like this as some sort of punishment.)
Mizuki: (I want to tell her that it's not her fault and she doesn't have to do this...)
Mizuki: (But I doubt that'll make her stop. It probably doesn't matter who tells her.)
Mizuki: (So at the very least...)
Mizuki: Um, Kanade...?
Kanade: Hm?
Mizuki: You keep saying that you haven't been able to save anyone yet.
Mizuki: But I can say for sure that you saved me. At least, the old me.
Kanade: Huh...?
Mizuki: Since I was little, I thought that living life was way too hard and really didn't like it.
Mizuki: Then, around junior high, I convinced myself that everything would be better if I just disappeared.
Mizuki: But that was when I heard one of your songs.
Mizuki: I felt that I'd found someone that was just like me.
Mizuki: I felt like trying a little harder after hearing it.
Kanade: Mizuki...
Kanade: Oh...
Mizuki: Hey, it's letting up! You think it'll stop soon?
Kanade: It looks like it. Everyone else is starting to put away their umbrellas.
Mizuki: Yay! All this rain's really been such a drag...
Mizuki: Speaking of which, there's actually one more spot that I want to show you. Wanna check it out since it's finally stopped raining?
Kanade: One more spot...?
Kanade: Sure, I'd like to see it. What's it like?
Mizuki: That's a secret! Well, not really. You can't actually hide a place like this...
Mizuki: It's that place with the fountain that's just nearby. It has all these little flowerbeds and looks so pretty♪
Mizuki: Look, you can sort of see it now!
Kanade: There? Huh? Wait...
Kanade: Those flowerbeds. Could it be...?
